24:00.960 --> 24:02.480
I think it's also worth highlighting

24:02.480 --> 24:04.880
some of the other reasons why Flatpak exists at all

24:04.880 --> 24:07.200
to begin with, or why other universal packaging formats

24:07.200 --> 24:08.240
do.

24:08.240 --> 24:10.480
